SELECT MIN(column_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

SELECT MAX(column_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

Example

  SELECT MIN(Price) AS SmallestPriceFROM Products;

Try it Yourself »

Here we use the MIN() function and the
GROUP BY clause, to return the smallest price 
for each category in the Products table:

Example

  SELECT MIN(Price) AS SmallestPrice, CategoryIDFROM ProductsGROUP BY CategoryID;

Try it Yourself »
